China Welcomes Iraq 's Decision to Resume Cooperation with UNSCOM
BEIJING , November 15 ( Xinhua ) -- The Chinese government today extended welcome to Iraq 's decision to unconditionally resume cooperation with the U.N. Special Commission ( UNSCOM ) and the International Atomic Energy Agency ( IAEA ) .
Upon reporters ' request to comment on Iraq 's decision to unconditionally resume cooperation with the two organizations , which was announced in a letter sent by Iraq 's Deputy Prime Minister Tareq Aziz to U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on Saturday , Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang said China hopes that Iraq will honor its commitment and earnestly implement relevant resolutions of the U.N. Security Council .
" We also hope that concerned parties will continue to make political and diplomatic efforts to seek an early solution to the weapons inspection crisis in Iraq , " he added .
Tang said that China has all along stood for a peaceful solution to the crisis and has maintained close contacts with relevant parties to seek a settlement of the crisis through political and diplomatic efforts .
He said that China , together with some other permanent members of the U.N. Security Council and relevant parties , has supported U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan to mediate the matter , and has played a constructive role in helping Annan to send a letter to Iraqi leaders .
